THIS IS WHERE THEY HEARTBREAKING

00:00:25.860 --> 00:00:26.790
STORY STARTED.

00:00:26.790 --> 00:00:29.030
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:00:29.030 --> 00:00:31.100
POLICE SAY A HOMELESS MAN DIED

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:32.130
HERE AND HIS DOG REFUSED TO

00:00:32.130 --> 00:00:33.730
LEAVE HIS SIDE.

00:00:33.730 --> 00:00:34.000
IT WAS CLOSE TO 100 DEGREES THAT

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:35.500
DAY.

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:39.500
AND EVEN THOUGH THE CANADIAN

00:00:39.500 --> 00:00:41.610
RIVER IS JUST A FEW FEET AWAY,

00:00:41.610 --> 00:00:46.080
HIS LOYAL BULL TERRIER REFUSED

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.780
TO LEAVE EVEN TO GET A DRINK.

00:00:48.780 --> 00:00:50.550
THIS LITTLE GUY DOESN'T QUITE

00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:52.680
SEEM TO KNOW WHY HE IS HERE.

00:00:52.680 --> 00:00:54.720
FRIDAY THIS BULL TERRIER HAS

00:00:54.720 --> 00:00:57.920
BEEN AT THE OKLAHOMA CITY ANIMAL

00:00:57.920 --> 00:00:58.320
SHELTER SHAKE IN HIS CAGE AND

00:00:58.320 --> 00:01:00.090
DEPRESSED.

00:01:00.090 --> 00:01:02.060
POLICE FOUND THE OWNER'S BODY BY

00:01:02.060 --> 00:01:03.090
THE RIVER WITH THE LOYAL

00:01:03.090 --> 00:01:05.430
COMPANION STANDING GUARD.

00:01:05.430 --> 00:01:07.730
THEY SAW A DOG POP OUT OF

00:01:07.730 --> 00:01:09.730
TREE LINE AND WHEN THEY LOOKED

00:01:09.730 --> 00:01:10.130
CLOSER THEY SAW A DECEASED

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:12.500
INDIVIDUAL.

00:01:12.500 --> 00:01:14.940
COME HERE, BUDDY.

00:01:14.940 --> 00:01:16.440
WENDY SAID THE LOUD BARKING

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:18.180
IS CONFUSING AND IT'S OBVIOUSLY

00:01:18.180 --> 00:01:20.340
HE KEEPS LOOKING FOR HIS OWNER.

00:01:20.340 --> 00:01:22.050
HE WAS WELL TAKEN CARE OF.

00:01:22.050 --> 00:01:24.180
THE OWNER LOVED HIM VERY MUCH.

00:01:24.180 --> 00:01:25.780
IT SHOWS IN HIS PERSONALITY

00:01:25.780 --> 00:01:26.220
BECAUSE HE DEFINITELY IS A

00:01:26.220 --> 00:01:30.250
PEOPLE DOG.

00:01:30.250 --> 00:01:32.220
THE ONLY TIME HE PERKS UP IS

00:01:32.220 --> 00:01:34.530
WHEN HE SEES HIS LEASH.

00:01:34.530 --> 00:01:37.400
IT'S THE ONE THING THAT STILL

00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:40.300
SMELLS LIKE HIS OWNER, HIS ONLY

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:42.130
COMFORT IN A PUZZLING WORLD.

00:01:42.130 --> 00:01:42.830
THE DOG WILL STAY UNTIL

00:01:42.830 --> 00:01:44.940
WEDNESDAY.

00:01:44.940 --> 00:01:47.170
FAMILY MEMBERS OF THE DECEASED

00:01:47.170 --> 00:01:48.010
HAVE UNTIL THAT TIME TO CLAIM

00:01:48.010 --> 00:01:51.380
THE DOG.

00:01:51.380 --> 00:01:53.410
AFTER THAT THE ANIMAL REFUGE

00:01:53.410 --> 00:01:55.110
CENTER WILL TAKE THE DOG OUT OF

00:01:55.110 --> 00:01:57.110
SHELTER AND PLACING HIM INTO A

00:01:57.110 --> 00:01:58.780
FOSTER HOME UNTIL A PERMANENT

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.600
FAMILY CAN BE FOUND FOR HIM.

